        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 10:07PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1007 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northwest of Dodson, or 8 miles east of Wellington, moving east
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dodson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
